comments: Nurkic (PHX) continues to move forward into Jones (SAS), initiating contact that causes him to trip.
Jones (SAS) walks beyond the three-point arc between free throws.
Allen (PHX) establishes himself in Johnson's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Durant's (PHX) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Vassell (SAS) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Okogie (PHX) during the jump shot attempt.
Okogie (PHX) reaches for the rebound and the contact with Vassell's (SAS) arm during the loose ball is marginal.
Okogie (PHX) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Jones (SAS) and Allen (PHX) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and Allen maintains possession of the ball.

Jones (SAS) jumps as Durant (PHX) turns and steps, resulting in incidental body contact. Jones then reaches for the ball when Durant brings it above his head, resulting in marginal contact, and Johnson (SAS) cleanly strips the ball.
Johnson (SAS) steals the ball away from Durant (PHX) and any contact that occurs is incidental.
Okogie (PHX) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Johnson's (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Watanabe (PHX) establishes himself in Johnson's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Durant's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
